  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      ABSTRACT

      Objectives: The aim of this article is to illustrate the possibility of performing a cochlear
      implant with local anesthesia and sedation, the anesthesic technique and the advantages of
      that in comparison to a general anesthesia.

      Materials and method: The investigators describe two successful surgeries done with local
      anesthesia, including the neural telemetry and the conditions the patient presented after the
      surgery, with a very good recovery and no complications during and after the procedure.

      Key words: local anesthesia, cochlear implant
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
